  <prompt>
    <goal>
      Create SkillEntity and SkillTypeReference DTO classes for deserializing Dataverse Web API responses.
    </goal>
    <context>
      Skills are stored in sprk_promptfragments entity with a lookup to sprk_aiskilltype.
      The DTOs will be used by GetSkillAsync to map Dataverse responses to domain models.

      Entity schema:
      - sprk_promptfragmentid (Guid)
      - sprk_name (String)
      - sprk_description (Memo)
      - sprk_promptfragment (Memo) - The actual skill prompt text
      - sprk_SkillTypeId (Lookup) â†’ sprk_aiskilltype
    </context>
    <constraints>
      - Use System.Text.Json attributes for property mapping
      - Follow existing ToolEntity pattern in ScopeResolverService
      - Keep DTOs as private nested classes
    </constraints>
  </prompt>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/patterns/dataverse/web-api-client.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/AI-ANALYSIS-PLAYBOOK-SCOPE-DESIGN.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">
      Review existing ToolEntity pattern:
      - Read ScopeResolverService.cs
      - Note DTO class structure
      - Note JsonPropertyName attributes
    </step>
    <step order="2">
      Create SkillEntity DTO class:
      - Add sprk_promptfragmentid as Id
      - Add sprk_name as Name
      - Add sprk_description as Description
      - Add sprk_promptfragment as PromptFragment
      - Add sprk_SkillTypeId as nested reference
    </step>
    <step order="3">
      Create SkillTypeReference DTO class:
      - Add sprk_name property for type name
    </step>
    <step order="4">
      Verify DTOs compile correctly:
      - Run dotnet build
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
